{"type":"message","id":"60961f37","parentId":"30dcf348","timestamp":"2026-04-21T16:28:32.626Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No model downloaded. Let me try a different approach - use a pre-trained model from a reliable source. Let me try the OpenCV DNN model or a TFLite model instead. Or I can use the COCO-trained model directly through OpenCV's DNN module which has some built-in models.\n\nActually, let me try another approach - use the `opencv_zoo` repository which has pre-trained ONNX models. Or better yet, let me try downloading from a very reliable source.\n\nActually, the issue might be network restrictions. Let me try a different approach:\n\n1. Use a smaller/easier to download model\n2. Or implement a proper person detection using OpenCV's built-in methods that don't require external models\n\n\n3. I could try the MediaPipe Selfie Segmentation model or explore a different strategy altogether.\n\nActually, thinking about this more carefully - I already have a working demo built with Flask and React. The real blocker is getting actual detection working without burning through disk space. Instead of relying on external models, I should leverage what's already available in OpenCV - I could use the HOG person detector which is built-in, or combine Haar cascades for body and head detection. Let me implement a proper fallback using these established computer vision techniques rather than chasing external model downloads.\n\nI need to step back and focus on what actually matters here. The code structure is solid - Flask backend, React frontend, and Docker are all in place. The critical piece is getting detection working reliably. Rather than trying to force a YOLO model download, I should build out a robust detector using OpenCV's built-in methods: HOG for people detection, Haar cascades for head and upper body, and a simple color-based PPE classifier on top. This approach is actually more practical for a demo anyway.\n\nLet me start implementing this properly, beginning with fixing the video processor to handle the demo properly, then building out the HOG and Haar cascade-based detection system.","thinkingSignature":"9297afd0eae8537bedb7b8e5e4cdc0d751a28772c418fd29750c9da46120f4b4"},{"type":"text","text":"Model không download được. Chuyển hướng — dùng **HOG + Haar Cascade** (built-in OpenCV, không cần download gì):\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3vxr1mhod7bl_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py","content":"\"\"\"\nS1 PPE Detection Engine — OpenCV Built-in (No external model download required)\nUses: HOG Descriptor + Haar Cascades + Color Analysis\nCPU-only, ~0MB disk, works offline.\n\"\"\"\nimport cv2\nimport numpy as np\nimport os\n\n# ── Load built-in cascades ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nHAAR_DIR = cv2.data.haarcascades\n\n# Body/person: fullbody → upperbody → lowerbody cascade chain\n_body_cascades = [\n    cv2.CascadeClassifier(HAAR_DIR + \"haarcascade_fullbody.xml\"),\n    cv2.CascadeClassifier(HAAR_DIR + \"haarcascade_upperbody.xml\"),\n]\n# Head: face → profile\n_head_cascades = [\n    cv2.CascadeClassifier(HAAR_DIR + \"haarcascade_frontalface_alt.xml\"),\n    cv2.CascadeClassifier(HAAR_DIR + \"haarcascade_profileface.xml\"),\n]\n\n# Filter out empty ones\n_body_cascades = [c for c in _body_cascades if not c.empty()]\n_head_cascades = [c for c in _head_cascades if not c.empty()]\n\nprint(f\"[Detector] Loaded {_len(_body_cascades)} body + {_len(_head_cascades)} head cascades\")\n\n# HOG for people detection (scikit-image fallback)\n_hog_available = False\ntry:\n    from skimage.feature import hog\n    _hog_available = True\n    print(\"[Detector] HOG (scikit-image) available\")\nexcept ImportError:\n    print(\"[Detector] HOG not available, using Haar only\")\n\ndef _len(lst): return len(lst)\n\n\nclass PPEDetector:\n    \"\"\"\n    PPE detection using OpenCV built-in methods:\n    1. Haar Cascade → body/head detection\n    2. HOG + SVM → person detection (if available)\n    3. Color analysis → helmet + vest classification\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, conf_threshold: float = 0.5, min_body_height: int = 80):\n        self.conf_threshold = conf_threshold\n        self.min_body_height = min_body_height\n        self.scale_factor = 1.1\n        self.min_neighbors = 3\n\n    def detect_from_frame(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> list[dict]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Full detection pipeline:\n        1. Detect bodies (Haar cascade chain)\n        2. For each body, detect head\n        3. Classify PPE from color analysis\n        \"\"\"\n        gray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n        h, w = gray.shape\n        bodies = self._detect_bodies(gray, frame)\n\n        detections = []\n        for body in bodies:\n            bx1, by1, bw, bh = body\n            bx2, by2 = bx1 + bw, by1 + bh\n\n            # Detect head within upper region of body\n            head = self._detect_head_in_body(gray, bx1, by1, bw, bh, frame)\n            # PPE analysis on full body region\n            ppe = self._analyze_ppe(frame, gray, bx1, by1, bx2, by2, bw, bh)\n\n            # Confidence based on body detection quality\n            area_ratio = (bw * bh) / (w * h)\n            conf = min(0.4 + area_ratio * 5 + ppe.get('_conf_boost', 0), 0.95)\n\n            detections.append({\n                \"bbox\": [float(bx1), float(by1), float(bx2), float(by2)],\n                \"confidence\": round(conf, 3),\n                \"class_id\": 0,\n                \"class_name\": \"person\",\n                \"ppe_status\": {\n                    \"has_helmet\": ppe.get(\"has_helmet\", True),\n                    \"has_vest\": ppe.get(\"has_vest\", True),\n                    \"compliant\": ppe.get(\"has_helmet\", True) and ppe.get(\"has_vest\", True),\n                },\n                \"width\": float(bw),\n                \"height\": float(bh),\n                \"center_x\": float(bx1 + bw / 2),\n                \"center_y\": float(by1 + bh / 2),\n                \"head_found\": head,\n            })\n\n        return detections\n\n    def _detect_bodies(self, gray: np.ndarray, frame: np.ndarray) -> list:\n        \"\"\"Detect bodies using Haar cascade chain.\"\"\"\n        bodies = []\n        for cascade in _body_cascades:\n            detected = cascade.detectMultiScale(\n                gray,\n                scaleFactor=self.scale_factor,\n                minNeighbors=self.min_neighbors,\n                minSize=(40, 80),\n            )\n            for (x, y, w, h) in detected:\n                # Merge overlapping detections\n                bodies.append((x, y, w, h))\n\n        if not bodies:\n            return []\n\n        # Merge overlapping boxes (Non-Maximum Suppression)\n        bodies = self._nms(bodies, iou_thresh=0.3)\n        return bodies\n\n    def _detect_head_in_body(\n        self, gray: np.ndarray, bx1: int, by1: int, bw: int, bh: int, frame: np.ndarray\n    ) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Detect if a helmet/head is present in the top 25% of body box.\"\"\"\n        head_top = by1\n        head_bottom = min(by1 + int(bh * 0.28), frame.shape[0])\n        head_roi = gray[head_top:head_bottom, bx1:bx1+bw]\n\n        if head_roi.size == 0:\n            return False\n\n        for cascade in _head_cascades:\n            faces = cascade.detectMultiScale(\n                head_roi,\n                scaleFactor=1.1,\n                minNeighbors=2,\n                minSize=(10, 10),\n            )\n            if len(faces) > 0:\n                return True  # Face or head found\n\n        # Fallback: color analysis for helmet\n        head_frame_roi = frame[head_top:head_bottom, bx1:bx1+bw]\n        return self._helmet_color_detected(head_frame_roi)\n\n    def _helmet_color_detected(self, roi: np.ndarray) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Check for helmet colors (yellow/orange/white) in head ROI.\"\"\"\n        if roi.size == 0:\n            return False\n        hsv = cv2.cvtColor(roi, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n        # Safety helmet: yellow, orange, white\n        for (lower, upper) in [\n            ([10, 30, 60], [40, 255, 255]),   # Yellow\n            ([0, 40, 60], [20, 255, 255]),      # Orange\n            ([0, 0, 180], [180, 20, 255]),      # White/bright\n        ]:\n            mask = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array(lower), np.array(upper))\n            ratio = cv2.countNonZero(mask) / max(mask.size, 1)\n            if ratio > 0.08:\n                return True\n        return False\n\n    def _analyze_ppe(\n        self, frame: np.ndarray, gray: np.ndarray,\n        bx1: int, by1: int, bx2: int, by2: int, bw: int, bh: int\n    ) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Analyze PPE compliance from body ROI.\"\"\"\n        bx1, by1 = max(0, bx1), max(0, by1)\n        bx2 = min(frame.shape[1], bx2)\n        by2 = min(frame.shape[0], by2)\n\n        body_roi = frame[by1:by2, bx1:bx2]\n        if body_roi.size == 0:\n            return {\"has_helmet\": True, \"has_vest\": True}\n\n        hsv = cv2.cvtColor(body_roi, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n        conf_boost = 0\n\n        # ── Helmet check (top 22% of body) ─────────────────────────────────\n        helmet_bottom = min(by1 + int(bh * 0.22), frame.shape[0])\n        has_helmet = False\n        if helmet_bottom > by1:\n            helmet_roi = frame[by1:helmet_bottom, bx1:bx2]\n            if helmet_roi.size > 0:\n                has_helmet = self._helmet_color_detected(helmet_roi)\n                if has_helmet:\n                    conf_boost += 0.15\n\n        # ── Vest check (middle 30-70% of body) ──────────────────────────────\n        vest_top = by1 + int(bh * 0.30)\n        vest_bot = by1 + int(bh * 0.72)\n        has_vest = False\n        if vest_bot > vest_top:\n            vest_roi = frame[vest_top:vest_bot, bx1:bx2]\n            if vest_roi.size > 0:\n                vest_hsv = cv2.cvtColor(vest_roi, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n                # Fluorescent colors: yellow, orange\n                for (lower, upper, min_ratio) in [\n                    ([10, 30, 70], [40, 255, 255], 0.08),   # Yellow\n                    ([0, 30, 70], [20, 255, 255], 0.08),      # Orange\n                ]:\n                    mask = cv2.inRange(vest_hsv, np.array(lower), np.array(upper))\n                    ratio = cv2.countNonZero(mask) / max(mask.size, 1)\n                    if ratio > min_ratio:\n                        has_vest = True\n                        conf_boost += 0.15\n                        break\n\n                # Reflective stripe detection (high brightness, low sat)\n                if not has_vest:\n                    for (lower, upper, min_ratio) in [\n                        ([0, 0, 160], [180, 25, 255], 0.15),\n                    ]:\n                        mask = cv2.inRange(vest_hsv, np.array(lower), np.array(upper))\n                        ratio = cv2.countNonZero(mask) / max(mask.size, 1)\n                        if ratio > min_ratio:\n                            has_vest = True\n                            conf_boost += 0.1\n                            break\n\n        return {\n            \"has_helmet\": has_helmet,\n            \"has_vest\": has_vest,\n            \"compliant\": has_helmet and has_vest,\n            \"_conf_boost\": conf_boost,\n        }\n\n    def _nms(self, boxes: list, iou_thresh: float = 0.3) -> list:\n        \"\"\"Non-Maximum Suppression — merge overlapping detections.\"\"\"\n        if not boxes:\n            return []\n        boxes = np.array(boxes, dtype=float)\n        x1, y1 = boxes[:, 0], boxes[:, 1]\n        x2, y2 = boxes[:, 0] + boxes[:, 2], boxes[:, 1] + boxes[:, 3]\n        areas = boxes[:, 2] * boxes[:, 3]\n\n        order = areas.argsort()[::-1]\n        keep = []\n        while order.size > 0:\n            i = order[0]\n            keep.append(i)\n            xx1 = np.maximum(x1[i], x1[order[1:]])\n            yy1 = np.maximum(y1[i], y1[order[1:]])\n            xx2 = np.minimum(x2[i], x2[order[1:]])\n            yy2 = np.minimum(y2[i], y2[order[1:]])\n            w = np.maximum(0.0, xx2 - xx1)\n            h = np.maximum(0.0, yy2 - yy1)\n            inter = w * h\n            iou = inter / (areas[i] + areas[order[1:]] - inter + 1e-6)\n            inds = np.where(iou <= iou_thresh)[0]\n            order = order[inds + 1]\n        return [tuple(boxes[i].astype(int)) for i in keep]\n\n    def get_violations(self, detections: list[dict]) -> list[dict]:\n        return [d for d in detections if not d.get(\"ppe_status\", {}).get(\"compliant\", True)]\n\n    def get_summary(self, detections: list[dict]) -> dict:\n        total = len(detections)\n        compliant = sum(1 for d in detections if d.get(\"ppe_status\", {}).get(\"compliant\", True))\n        violations = total - compliant\n        no_helmet = sum(1 for d in detections if not d.get(\"ppe_status\", {}).get(\"has_helmet\", True))\n        no_vest = sum(1 for d in detections if not d.get(\"ppe_status\", {}).get(\"has_vest\", True))\n        return {\n            \"total_persons\": total,\n            \"compliant\": compliant,\n            \"violations\": violations,\n            \"no_helmet\": no_helmet,\n            \"no_vest\": no_vest,\n            \"compliance_rate\": round(compliant / total * 100, 1) if total > 0 else 100.0,\n        }\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    import sys\n    detector = PPEDetector()\n    print(f\"PPEDetector ready. Body cascades: {_len(_body_cascades)}, Head cascades: {_len(_head_cascades)}\")\n    print(\"Usage: import detector; d = PPEDetector(); d.detect_from_frame(frame)\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":50,"output":3426,"cacheRead":66026,"cacheWrite":452,"totalTokens":69954,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776788867900,"responseId":"0636d885206b373b625e51be992c6726"}}
