{"type":"message","id":"551482cf","parentId":"e7d8f1dd","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:06:34.535Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It's going through Flask (Werkzeug server) because the Vite proxy is forwarding `/video` to Flask. The video in `public/video/` is not being served by Vite because the proxy matches first.\n\nLet me check - in Vite's config, the proxy for `/video` sends to Flask. But if Vite's dev server has the file in `public/video/demo.mp4`, it should serve it directly without proxy.\n\nActually, the issue might be that Vite's dev server proxies `/video` to Flask BEFORE checking its own public directory. In Vite, the proxy has higher priority than local files.\n\n\nI need to either remove the `/video` proxy from Vite entirely so it serves the file from `public/` instead, or verify the public folder structure is correct.","thinkingSignature":"b93fd7439a1b0f38271cb3ce0afbf8c815fec29aad3fe4def6deaf92c5fbe577"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wbgac40imysn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":125,"output":219,"cacheRead":124798,"cacheWrite":471,"totalTokens":125613,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776791186861,"responseId":"0636e194660101401053e8c6850630a9"}}
