{"type":"message","id":"00361b47","parentId":"1ed504c4","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:18:50.863Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Nginx is not installed. Let me install it, or alternatively use Python's built-in HTTP server to serve the video. Actually, the simplest solution might be to use Flask-SocketIO's underlying Werkzeug server properly. But the real issue might be that Flask-SocketIO is wrapping the Flask app and intercepting routes.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach - use Python's built-in http.server to serve the video on a different port, and have the frontend load from that.Actually, even simpler: let me just make the video URL point to a Python HTTP server that serves the file. Or even simpler: use a direct data URL... but the video is 700KB which is too big.\n\n\nI could copy the video to the frontend's public folder and serve it from there instead. Actually, wait - the frontend dev server should be able to handle this through the `/video` proxy route, but I removed that earlier. Let me just add it back since Vite is more reliable for static file serving anyway.\n\nThough even with the proxy in place, the browser might still be blocking it due to how Werkzeug handles Range requests - those are critical for HTML5 video to work properly. Let me test if a regular fetch succeeds even though the video element fails.\n\nThe most straightforward fix is probably to either install nginx for proper static file serving, use Flask with gunicorn for better Range request support, or just serve the video directly from the frontend's public folder and bypass the backend entirely. I should try the public folder approach first since it avoids the proxy complexity altogether.\n\nBut I'm realizing there might be a bigger issue here - when the frontend is served from port 3003, it's at `http://103.253.21.139:3003`, and the video is at `http://103.253.21.139:5000`. That's a different origin, so CORS headers would matter. Though I did add `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` to the Flask response, so that should be fine.\n\nLet me check what the actual error is. The video error handler just logs to console, but if I can see the network error in the browser, that would tell me what's really going wrong.\n\nActually, I think the simplest solution is to serve the video directly from the frontend's public folder instead of proxying through Flask. I just need to make sure the video file is actually in that public directory.","thinkingSignature":"ed2f19f3bb9103a16c13dc354965821e30f935aed26fd736e05fce7da9e1e141"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hvkgpw33vpnu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if public folder serves correctly\ncurl -sI http://localhost:3003/video/demo.mp4 | head -5\necho \"---\"\n# Install gunicorn for better static file serving\npip3 install gunicorn -q 2>&1 | tail -2\nwhich gunicorn","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":54,"output":593,"cacheRead":148345,"cacheWrite":1778,"totalTokens":150770,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776791916581,"responseId":"0636e46e458753cb3f68b8f2e3cca82b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd03d8b8","parentId":"00361b47","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:18:54.231Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hvkgpw33vpnu_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nVary: Origin\r\nserver: Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12\r\ndate: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:18:50 GMT, Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:18:50 GMT\r\ncontent-disposition: inline; filename=demo.mp4\r\n---\nWARNING: Running pip as the 'root' user can result in broken permissions and conflicting behaviour with the system package manager. It is recommended to use a virtual environment instead: https://pip.pypa.io/warnings/venv\n/usr/local/bin/gunicorn"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3311,"aggregated":"HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nVary: Origin\r\nserver: Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12\r\ndate: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:18:50 GMT, Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:18:50 GMT\r\ncontent-disposition: inline; filename=demo.mp4\r\n---\nWARNING: Running pip as the 'root' user can result in broken permissions and conflicting behaviour with the system package manager. It is recommended to use a virtual environment instead: https://pip.pypa.io/warnings/venv\n/usr/local/bin/gunicorn","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776791934211}}
{"type":"message","id":"693e6f9a","parentId":"bd03d8b8","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:19:01.612Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the Vite dev server IS proxying to Flask. The video is served by Flask via the proxy. The issue is that the browser can't load the video even though curl can.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The problem might be that the Flask-SocketIO app wraps the Flask app and somehow interferes with static file serving. Or the Werkzeug dev server has issues with video streaming.\n\nActually, let me try using gunicorn with the Flask-SocketIO app. Gunicorn handles static files and streaming much better than the Werkzeug dev server.","thinkingSignature":"4d2a9765be0fb76076c5262dbfb8af97f41bac8fe3c380842d8545058929a451"},{"type":"text","text":"Dùng **gunicorn** thay Flask dev server — xử lý video streaming tốt hơn nhiều:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lhn9jborq6ds_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pip3 install gunicorn -q 2>&1 | tail -1 && gunicorn --version","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":179,"output":202,"cacheRead":149598,"cacheWrite":1140,"totalTokens":151119,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776791934265,"responseId":"0636e48122944706a18e8e9009dc3d21"}}
{"type":"message","id":"658df390","parentId":"693e6f9a","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:19:03.834Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lhn9jborq6ds_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"WARNING: Running pip as the 'root' user can result in broken permissions and conflicting behaviour with the system package manager. It is recommended to use a virtual environment instead: https://pip.pypa.io/warnings/venv\ngunicorn (version 25.3.0)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2184,"aggregated":"WARNING: Running pip as the 'root' user can result in broken permissions and conflicting behaviour with the system package manager. It is recommended to use a virtual environment instead: https://pip.pypa.io/warnings/venv\ngunicorn (version 25.3.0)","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776791943818}}
{"type":"message","id":"9023e1f1","parentId":"658df390","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:19:13.840Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, gunicorn doesn't work well with Flask-SocketIO directly. Flask-SocketIO requires an async framework. Let me think about this differently.\n\nActually, the simplest fix is to just serve the video directly from the frontend public folder via the Vite dev server. The problem was that when the frontend is in dev mode, it proxies to Flask. But if we serve the video from the frontend's own public folder, it should work.\n\nBut wait - I removed the `/video` proxy from the Vite config. Let me add it back and also configure it to NOT proxy but instead serve from public.Actually, Vite dev server doesn't proxy `/video` - it serves from `public/` folder. \n\nSo the solution is straightforward: put the video in the frontend's `public/video/` directory and access it via `/video/demo.mp4`. I already have it there, so I just need to add the proxy back to Vite config to route `/video` requests to the Flask backend instead.","thinkingSignature":"653e99b74d5a29900297c878a9ae31d18a887b13b919b1b44e3b153c77d15c7e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_upcdjn9astxn_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/vite.config.js","edits":[{"oldText":"      '/socket.io': {\n        target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n        ws: true,\n      },","newText":"      '/video': {\n        target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n        changeOrigin: true,\n        // Don't buffer video - stream it\n        configure: (proxy) => {\n          proxy.on('proxyReq', (proxyReq, req, res) => {\n            // Let Flask handle Range requests natively\n          })\n        }\n      },\n      '/socket.io': {\n        target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n        ws: true,\n      },"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":105,"output":408,"cacheRead":150140,"cacheWrite":947,"totalTokens":151600,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776791943848,"responseId":"0636e4894e012adf80160cdb48f85e32"}}
{"type":"message","id":"74df0788","parentId":"9023e1f1","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:19:13.903Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_upcdjn9astxn_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/vite.config.js."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  9       '/api': {\n 10         target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n 11         changeOrigin: true,\n 12       },\n+13       '/video': {\n+14         target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n+15         changeOrigin: true,\n+16         // Don't buffer video - stream it\n+17         configure: (proxy) => {\n+18           proxy.on('proxyReq', (proxyReq, req, res) => {\n+19             // Let Flask handle Range requests natively\n+20           })\n+21         }\n+22       },\n 13       '/socket.io': {\n 14         target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n 15         ws: true,\n 16       },\n    ...","firstChangedLine":13},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776791953885}}
{"type":"message","id":"8aeba2cb","parentId":"74df0788","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:19:23.137Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but this still uses Flask. The issue is likely that Flask-SocketIO interferes with Flask's `send_from_directory`. Let me think about this differently.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach. Let me serve the video from a Python simple HTTP server on a different port, just for the video.Actually, even simpler: let me just change the VIDEO_URL to point to the frontend's public folder directly (not through proxy). In Vite dev mode, files in `public/` are served at the root. So `/video/demo.mp4` should serve from `public/video/demo.mp4` directly without any proxy!\n\nWait, but when I removed the `/video` proxy earlier, it DID serve from public (200 OK with Vite's headers). But the browser still couldn't load it...\n \nLet me check if Flask is actually the one intercepting the `/video` route. The Flask backend's `serve_video` route is still registered, so even though I removed the proxy, Flask is handling that path instead of Vite serving from public. I need to either disable that Flask route or change the video URL to something that won't hit Flask.\n\nActually, the simplest fix is to serve the video from a completely different path that Flask won't intercept—something like `/static/video.mp4`—and update the frontend to use that URL instead.","thinkingSignature":"6aa73a60ec937cd2a736f8b55d957fbd1235aa049b9fea295560ce3e8103e7c2"},{"type":"text","text":"Vấn đề là Flask đang intercept `/video`. Đổi route sang path khác:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7btfkc5pfvze_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n '\"/video/<path:filename>\"' /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/app.py","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":77,"output":363,"cacheRead":150880,"cacheWrite":688,"totalToken